theorem
(seq is  bounded implies ( a * seq ) is  bounded)
proof
deffunc 09(RealUnitarySpace) = ( 0. $1 );
assume seq is  bounded;
then consider M such that A1: M > ( 0 ) and A2: (for n holds ||. ( seq . n ) .|| <= M) by CKB21:def 1;
A3: (a <> ( 0 ) implies ( a * seq ) is  bounded)
proof
A4:now
let n;
A5: ( abs a ) >= ( 0 ) by COMPLEX1:46;
||. ( ( a * seq ) . n ) .|| = ||. ( a * ( seq . n ) ) .|| by NORMSP_1:def 5
.= ( ( abs a ) * ||. ( seq . n ) .|| ) by BHSP_1:27;
hence ||. ( ( a * seq ) . n ) .|| <= ( ( abs a ) * M ) by A2,A5,XREAL_1:64;
end;
assume a <> ( 0 );
then ( abs a ) > ( 0 ) by COMPLEX1:47;
then ( ( abs a ) * M ) > ( 0 ) by A1,XREAL_1:129;
hence thesis by A4,CKB21:def 1;
end;
(a = ( 0 ) implies ( a * seq ) is  bounded)
proof
assume A6: a = ( 0 );
now
let n;
||. ( ( a * seq ) . n ) .|| = ||. ( ( 0 ) * ( seq . n ) ) .|| by A6,NORMSP_1:def 5
.= ||. 09(X) .|| by RLVECT_1:10
.= ( 0 ) by BHSP_1:26;
hence ||. ( ( a * seq ) . n ) .|| <= M by A1;
end;
hence thesis by A1,CKB21:def 1;
end;
hence thesis by A3;
end;
